{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Arrange courgettes cut side down in Varoma dish and tray (ensuring that some air holes are left clear).","Arrange aubergines and onions on top.","Place water in mixing bowl, place covered Varoma into position, then steam <nobr>20 min\/Varoma\/speed 1<\/nobr>. Remove Varoma and empty mixing bowl.","Set vegetables aside to cool (approx. 10 minutes). Meanwhile, preheat oven to 180°C and grease baking tray.","Remove vegetable flesh with a tablespoon, without splitting skin. Place vegetable flesh in mixing bowl.","Add olive oil, breadcrumbs, milk, basil, egg, salt and pepper in mixing bowl then mix <nobr>3 sec\/speed 5<\/nobr>.","Place vegetables skins, hollowed side up, on prepared baking tray. Spread filling in hollowed-out vegetables and drizzle with remaining 1 Tbsp oil. Bake for 20-30 minutes (180°C) until golden brown. Serve hot."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["2 courgettes (approx. 400 g), halved lengthways","2 aubergines (approx. 500 g), halved lengthways","2 white onions (approx. 240 g), halved","500 g water","10 g extra virgin olive oil, plus 1 Tbsp and extra for greasing","100 g breadcrumbs","20 g milk","10 fresh basil leaves","1 large egg","½ tsp fine sea salt","1 pinch ground black pepper"]}],"id":"r120118","imageLink":"https:\/\/3.bp.blogspot.com\/-OKA6JwLJojg\/XZVPMMMwpQI\/AAAAAAAAc2E\/bmfbDCd41XQ5LZrOd1VlzQTVCRJ3vzlhgCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_2KhZONzD9kcxLuUf.png","title":"Stuffed Vegetables","publishedAt":"2016-06-06T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"6.1 g","fat":"5.2 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"16.2 g","calories":"567 kJ \/ 136 kcal"},"usefulItems":"baking tray, oven","hintsAndTricks":["30 g Parmesan could be added in step 5 but will add extra calories!<br>","For a gluten free version omit the breadcrumbs and experiment with adding your favourite cooked grains in step 6.<br>"],"basicInfo":["easy","15m","1h 5m","4 portions"]}